    <stitle>CAB: 5000i AND 9000i CONVENTIONAL - REMOVE - Remove DRIVER AND PASSENGER SEATS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x1602102" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Remove DRIVER AND PASSENGER SEATS</title>
        <para>Individual air suspension driver and passenger seats, and mechanical passenger seats are available on this
            cab
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1602129">(Figure 29)</hotlnk>
            and
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1602130">(Figure 30)</hotlnk>, with additional seat options available for the driver. Both
            driver and passenger seats provide many seat and back rest adjustments to assure a comfortable ride.
        </para>
        <para>Refer to seat manufacturer's information for additional seat specific details.</para>
        <figure id="f1602129" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602129.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="368px"
                     scalefitheight="392px"/>
            <caption>Figure 29. Driver Seat</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. DRIVER SEAT ASSEMBLY (BOSTON 914 SHOWN)</callout1>
                <callout1>2. NYLON TUBING (AIR LINE)</callout1>
                <callout1>3. SEAT MOUNTING BOLT</callout1>
                <callout1>4. FLOOR MAT TRIM PANEL</callout1>
                <callout1>5. "WEST COASTER" MOUNTING</callout1>
                <callout1>6. DURAFORM FLEETCRUISER MOUNTING</callout1>
                <callout1>7. NATIONAL "CUSH-IN-AIR" MOUNTING</callout1>
                <callout1>8. "BOSTROM" MODEL 914 MOUNTING</callout1>
                <callout1>9. "UNISON AIR RIDE" MOUNTING</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1602130" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602130.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="208px"
                     scalefitheight="472px"/>
            <caption>Figure 30. Passenger Seat</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. PASSENGER SEAT ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>2. MOUNTING BOLT</callout1>
                <callout1>3. MOUNTING BOLT</callout1>
                <callout1>4. SEAT MOUNTING BASE</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1602129">Figure 29</hotlnk>
            for Items in parentheses.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 2 mounting bolts from each side of seat and remove seat belt brackets from seat.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove driver seat assembly (Item 1) by removing 4 seat mounting bolts (Item 3) which secure
                seat pedestal to floor. If seat is air suspension type, be sure to disconnect air line (Item 2) before
                lifting out seat assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1602130">Figure 30</hotlnk>
            for Items in parentheses.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove passenger seat assembly (Item 1) by removing 4 mounting bolts (Items 2 and 3) which
                secure seat frame. If seat is air suspension type, be sure to disconnect air line before lifting out
                seat assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Clean seat suspension and adjusters as required by wiping away any grease or dirt with shop towel.
                    Apply a light coat of multipurpose lube to pivot points, sliding areas and rollers to assure a
                    smooth operation on reinstallation. Wipe away excess lube.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
